<TITLE> Primary probe report of NCTB fire 'in three days' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com) - A seven-member probe team has been formed to investigate the devastating fire at the National Curriculum and Textbook Board's Tejgaon warehouse on Sunday, said a government statement. The committee, headed by Razia Begum, additional secretary of education ministry, has been given three days to submit a primary report of their findings on the cause of the fire, an estimate of the losses incurred and those responsible, if any. A detailed report is to be submitted twelve days after the primary report, said the statement issued on Sunday evening as stacks of books and paper continued to smoulder twelve hours after the fire broke out at 7am. Other members of the committee are ATM Mohiuddin Ahmed, joint secretary of the education ministry, other officials of education and home ministries and representatives from the finance section of NCTB, the secondary and higher education directorate and fire service and civil defence directorate. The committee is also empowered to co-opt further members according to need. The Tejgaon warehouse is the main store for paper for government textbooks and other books. Another NCTB warehouse is situated at Tongi. bdnews24
